{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcwaJTNjxvHvEzzJ3oVGT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014eTZ4gz9qcfepZns4xvqgq","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2v2-f46b83c8-without-lessons-ledger--ll1-r1/memory/staging-debug-swallows-errors.md","content":"---\nname: staging-debug-swallows-errors\ndescription: Staging config with DEBUG=true silently swallows all errors — debugging gotcha\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nStaging config had `DEBUG=true`, which silently swallowed all errors and made a bug nearly impossible to trace. Cost ~2 hours of debugging (2026-07-11).\n\n**Why:** With DEBUG=true, errors are suppressed rather than surfaced, so failures look like silent no-ops instead of raising/logging.\n\n**How to apply:** When errors are mysteriously vanishing in staging (or any env), check the DEBUG flag in that environment's config first before deep-diving. It was fixed by setting DEBUG=false in staging.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":823,"cache_read_input_tokens":20506,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":823},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aca878aa-33cb-4522-804d-fdb9b855bc23","uuid":"43828734-c877-4689-9089-9b20393cd1d0","request_id":"req_011CcwaJSNxkxQsKjVV7cu3N"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014eTZ4gz9qcfepZns4xvqgq","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2v2-f46b83c8-without-lessons-ledger--ll1-r1/memory/staging-debug-swallows-errors.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aca878aa-33cb-4522-804d-fdb9b855bc23","uuid":"2ca968ce-1956-4efb-ac5d-1dc4babaf008","timestamp":"2026-07-12T05:00:57.019Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2v2-f46b83c8-without-lessons-ledger--ll1-r1/memory/staging-debug-swallows-errors.md","content":"---\nname: staging-debug-swallows-errors\ndescription: Staging config with DEBUG=true silently swallows all errors — debugging gotcha\nmetadata: \n  node_type: memory\n  type: project\n  originSessionId: aca878aa-33cb-4522-804d-fdb9b855bc23\n---\n\nStaging config had `DEBUG=true`, which silently swallowed all errors and made a bug nearly impossible to trace. Cost ~2 hours of debugging (2026-07-11).\n\n**Why:** With DEBUG=true, errors are suppressed rather than surfaced, so failures look like silent no-ops instead of raising/logging.\n\n**How to apply:** When errors are mysteriously vanishing in staging (or any env), check the DEBUG flag in that environment's config first before deep-diving. It was fixed by setting DEBUG=false in staging.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
